Rebased past #21727.

> I'm not convinced that a `VersionBitsCache` class is necessary.

@jnewbery - You're right it's not necessary; but I think minimising the number of globals and keeping the lock and the things the lock is guarding together (which then allows stronger locking assertions, see https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20272#issuecomment-720755781) is worthwhile enough. If you're implying the `ComputeBlockVersion` to `versionbits.ComputeBlockVersion` change is a bit ugly, that could be fixed just by adding an `inline int32_t ComputeBlockVersion(pindexPrev, params) { return versionbits.ComputeBlockVersion(pindexPrev, params); }` in deploymentstatus.h (where the `versionbits` global is declared).

